Description: Repaint the selection as it changes during interaction
 FOX releases queued repaints only when the connection goes idle, so a
 selection drag starves them and the accumulated damage merges into
 wide bands that repaint in visible jumps. Dispatch the pending
 repaint after each selection extension, as the icon list already does
 mid-drag, so the highlight tracks the mouse and each repaint covers
 only the newly changed span. Also skip the active-row repaints when
 the active background matches the plain one and no styles are set,
 since they redraw identical pixels.
Author: Logan Russell <me@lrussell.net>
